SECRET_KEY=your-secret-key-here
DEBUG=True
ALLOWED_HOSTS=localhost,127.0.0.1

python -c "from django.core.management.utils import get_random_secret_key; print(get_random_secret_key())" This command generates a random secret key for your Django project. You can run this command in your terminal, and it will output a new secret key that you can use in your .env file. Just copy the generated key and replace the placeholder in your .env file with it.